**1. After the callback, does Arthur Core exchange the authorization code with Ping and store the access, ID and refresh tokens in Redis?**

Yes. After Ping redirects back to Arthur Core on `/auth/callback`, Arthur Core exchanges the authorization code with Ping using the token endpoint.

Arthur Core receives the token response from Ping, extracts the user identity from the ID token, loads the user and sales-point context from Partner Repository, and creates an Arthur session in Redis.

At the moment, Arthur Core stores the access token and refresh token in the Redis-backed Arthur session. The ID token is used to extract claims and can be stored if required, but it should not be shared with B2Boost.

**2. Does B2Boost receive any Ping token, or only a security context generated by Arthur Core?**

B2Boost receives only the security context generated by Arthur Core.

B2Boost does **not** receive the Ping access token, ID token, or refresh token.

The browser/form submit carries only a temporary one-time handoff code. B2Boost then exchanges that code with Arthur Core server-to-server to retrieve the security context.

**3. What exact data is included in the security context transferred to B2Boost?**

The current security context returned by Arthur Core contains:

